# Local Dev — Agent Must NOT Run Servers

## HARD BAN (no exceptions)

The agent must **NEVER** use the Shell tool to run any of these:

- `npm run dev`
- `npm run preview`
- `vite`
- `npx vite`
- Any command whose purpose is starting a local HTTP dev server

This applies even when the user says: deploy, launch, run locally, let me see it, start the server.

**The user starts the server themselves in their own terminal.** The agent only prints the command.

## What the agent should do instead

Reply with exactly this workflow (copy/paste for the user):

```
cd C:\Users\jordan77\Documents\GitHub\Tripreport\app
npm run dev
```

Tell them: open port **5173** in Chrome, Edge, or Firefox (not Cursor's built-in browser).

Do NOT include a clickable `http://` link — that can open Cursor's Simple Browser and crash the session.

## Also banned (causes hangs and extra processes)

- `Await` / `AwaitShell` on terminal output
- `Start-Sleep` to wait for a server
- Running `npm run lint` or `npm run build` in the same turn as any server command
- Starting a second server without the user asking to kill the first

## If processes piled up

Tell the user to run in their terminal:

```
cd C:\Users\jordan77\Documents\GitHub\Tripreport
npm run kill-dev
```

The agent may run `npm run kill-dev` once to help cleanup — that is allowed. The agent must NOT run `npm run dev` afterward.
